  "A US company imports electronics from Japan. The current rate is 1 USD = 150 JPY. If the dollar weakens to 1 USD = 120 JPY, how does this affect the cost of a 300,000 JPY shipment in US dollars?": "",
  "Cost stays at $2,000": "",
  "Cost increases from $2,000 to $3,000": "",
  "Cost decreases from $2,000 to $1,500": "",
  "Cost increases from $2,000 to $2,500": "",
  "At 150 JPY/USD: 300,000 / 150 = $2,000. At 120 JPY/USD: 300,000 / 120 = $2,500. The weaker dollar means the company pays $500 more for the same shipment, a 25% cost increase.": "",
